body:
Hi! I tried force instantsearch to work with IE11. I rewrite all backticks and arrow functions, but i have some weird errors. When i comment those parts algolia starts so i hope i am close to success. 

First errors is problem with transformData. My code is  like:

```
transformData: {
        item(item) {
          //console.log(item);
          /* eslint-disable no-param-reassign */
          item.price = priceReplace(item.price);
          item.starsLayout = getStarsHTML(item.rating);
          return item;
        },
      },
```

IE told me it expect ':' here -> 'item(item)'. I have 4 widgets with transformData and i really need it. 
There is the same story:

```
tooltips: {
        format(rawValue) { <- "expected :"
          return Math.round(rawValue).toLocaleString()+'zł';
        },
      },
```

I had a little problem with arrow functions. On normal browserw it works but IE dont like it:

`const itemsHTML = items.map(function({ value, label, isRefined }){`
I got error like : "Expected identifier".

there is full code:

```
//CUSTOM HITS PER PAGE WIDGET
  // custom 'renderFn' to render the custom HitsPerPage widget
  function renderFn2(HitsPerPageRenderingOptions, isFirstRendering) {
    var containerNode = HitsPerPageRenderingOptions.widgetParams.containerNode;
    var items = HitsPerPageRenderingOptions.items;
    var refine = HitsPerPageRenderingOptions.refine;

    const itemsHTML = items.map(function({ value, label, isRefined }){
      const button = document.createElement("button");
      button.addEventListener("click", function(){refine(value)});
      button.className = isRefined ? "refined" : "";
      button.textContent = label;
      return button;
    });

    containerNode.innerText = "";
    itemsHTML.forEach(function(item){containerNode.appendChild(item)});
  }

  // connect 'renderFn' to HitsPerPage logic
  var customHitsPerPage = instantsearch.connectors.connectHitsPerPage(renderFn2);

  // mount widget on the page
  search.addWidget(
    customHitsPerPage({
      containerNode: document.getElementById("hits-per-page-selector"),
      items: [
        { value: 24, label: "24", default: true },
        { value: 96, label: "96" },
      ],
    })
  );
```
